branchCategory.name: 25A-LEY Electric Actuator, Rod Type, AC Servo Motor, Secondary Battery
branchCategory.description: The 25A- series variations are compatible with secondary battery manufacturing for electronics, automotive, and other vehicle types. Design goals include eliminating copper (Cu) and zinc (Zn) materials where possible, and employing a low dew point grease that retains lubricity even in low manufacturing termpertures. Please note the copper and zinc materials are used for the motors, cables, controllers and drivers.
branchCategory.bullets: <UL><LI>Same features and performance as standard LEY <LI>Stainless steel bolts for construction <LI>Low dew point grease functional down to -70°C <LI>Copper and zinc free except for motor, cables, and controller <LI>Alloy steel rod bearing, replaces bronze bearing <LI>Non-standard materials for compatibility with secondary/rechargeable battery manufacturing</LI></UL>
